GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
SESSION 2025
H 1
HOUSE BILL 1067
Short Title: Rural Hall/Elections/Unaffiliated Candidates. (Local)
Sponsors: Representative K. Hall.
For a complete list of sponsors, refer to the North Carolina General Assembly web site.
Referred to: Election Law, if favorable, Rules, Calendar, and Operations of the House
April 29, 2026
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO AMEND THE CHARTER OF THE TOWN OF RURAL HALL TO ESTABLISH
3 A UNIFORM PROCESS FOR THE ELECTION OF UNAFFILIATED CANDIDATES IN
4 MUNICIPAL ELECTIONS.
5 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
6 SECTION 1. The Charter of the Town of Rural Hall, being Chapter 1100 of the 1973
7 Session Laws, is amended by adding a new section to read:
8 "Sec. 4.1. Any unaffiliated candidate seeking nomination by petition for municipal office
9 shall comply with the requirements of Article 11 of Chapter 163 of the General Statutes, provided
10 the Forsyth County board of elections may prescribe rules and regulations governing the
11 following:
12 (1) Setting the date and time that completed petitions must be timely submitted
13 for verification.
14 (2) Stating the information that shall be set out in the petition to be signed by the
15 voters requesting a person be a candidate for any such office, such as the
16 giving of the full name of every such voter, the street address of such voter,
17 or any other pertinent information required to facilitate the checking of such
18 petition against the registration books."
19 SECTION 2. This act is effective when it becomes law and applies to elections held
20 on or after that date.
*H1067-v-1*

